        <div>
          <h4>LA craft-cocktail bars</h4>
          <p><a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood</a>, <a href="/hollywood/">Hollywood</a>, DTLA, Santa
          Monica, Culver City, Arts District speakeasies. Smaller tap counts (4-12), premium glass and faucet
          hardware, integrated back-bar refrigeration. Perlick is the default spec in this tier.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>LA brewery tap rooms</h4>
          <p>Arts District, East LA, <a href="/culver-city/">Culver City</a>, Inglewood, <a href="/long-beach/">Long Beach</a>,
          Torrance brewing corridor. Large tap counts (20-40), long trunk runs from cold storage to tap walls,
          extended service hours. Heaviest Perlick-system service dispatch.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Fine-dining restaurant bars</h4>
          <p>Westside, DTLA, Beverly Hills fine-dining bar programs with premium draft integration. Usually
          8-14 taps with a craft-beer + wine-on-tap + kombucha hybrid program.</p>
        </div>
